												<p>Ed Simon is the Public Humanities Special Faculty in the English Department of Carnegie Mellon University, a staff writer for Lit Hub, and the editor of <em>Belt Magazine</em>. His most recent book is <em>Devil's Contract: The History of the Faustian Bargain</em>, the first comprehensive, popular account of that subject.</p>
